(40, 4, 2, 5, 9, 9, 9, 'forty days and forty nights', 'Fasting for Forty Days', 'This connection highlights the theme of fasting for forty days and nights in both passages. Matthew 4:2 describes Jesus fasting, while Deuteronomy 9:9 recounts Moses doing the same during his time on the mountain.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 4, 2, 2, 24, 18, 18, 'forty days and forty nights', 'Fasting and Divine Encounter', 'Both passages emphasize a period of forty days and nights, highlighting a significant time of preparation and divine encounter. In Matthew, Jesus fasts, while in Exodus, Moses communes with God, suggesting a connection in their spiritual journeys.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 4, 2, 41, 11, 12, 12, 'an hungred', 'Connection of Hunger in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of hunger experienced by Jesus. In Matthew, he is hungry after fasting, while in Mark, he is hungry after traveling from Bethany.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 4, 3, 1, 3, 1, 5, 'If thou be the Son of God', 'Temptation and Doubt', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of temptation, where the tempter challenges the identity and authority of God. In Matthew, the tempter questions Jesus'' identity as the Son of God, similar to how the serpent questions God''s command in Genesis.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 4, 3, 52, 3, 5, 5, 'the tempter', 'Connection of Temptation Themes', 'This connection highlights the theme of temptation present in both passages. In Matthew, the tempter directly challenges Jesus, while in 1 Thessalonians, Paul expresses concern about the potential for the tempter to lead the Thessalonians astray.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 4, 3, 4, 11, 4, 6, 'command that these stones be made bread', 'Desire for Physical Sustenance', 'Both passages emphasize a longing for physical food. In Matthew, the tempter challenges Jesus to turn stones into bread, while in Numbers, the Israelites express a desire for the flesh and vegetables they had in Egypt, contrasting it with the manna provided to them.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 4, 3, 42, 22, 31, 32, 'If thou be the Son of God', 'Connection of Temptation and Faith', 'This connection highlights the theme of spiritual testing. In Matthew, the tempter challenges Jesus'' identity, while in Luke, Satan seeks to test Simon''s faith. Both passages emphasize the struggle against temptation and the importance of faith.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
